DataFeature.Name: Electromagnetic Compatibility
DataFeature.Definition: The ability of the product to function properly in the presence of electromagnetic interference.
DataFeature.SourceDescription: This data feature is extracted from the input text, which states the product's compliance with the EMC directive.

EvaluatedAnnotations.Name: electromagnetic compatibility
EvaluatedAnnotations.Definition: ability of an electric facility to function satisfactorily in its electromagnetic environment without affecting this environment in an inadmissible fashion
EvaluatedAnnotations.Reason: The given annotation is relevant as it provides a general definition of electromagnetic compatibility.

EvaluatedAnnotations.Name: Electromagnetic Compatibility (EMC standard)
EvaluatedAnnotations.Definition: shock resistance of electrical and electronic devices to electromagnetic faults, which are defined for different environments (such as industrial environments or home and business environments) and with multiple severity classifications
EvaluatedAnnotations.Reason: The given annotation is not relevant as it focuses on the shock resistance aspect of electromagnetic compatibility, which is not the main focus of the data feature.

EvaluatedAnnotations.Name: classification of electromagnetic compatibility
EvaluatedAnnotations.Definition: classification of the ability of measuring equipment or a measuring system to operate as specified in its electromagnetic environment without introducing intolerable electromagnetic disturbances to anything in that environment
EvaluatedAnnotations.Reason: The given annotation is not relevant as it focuses on the classification aspect of electromagnetic compatibility, which is not the main focus of the data feature.

EvaluatedAnnotations.Name: EMC design present
EvaluatedAnnotations.Definition: Design in electromagnetic compatibility, i.e. there is no build-up of interfering electromagnetic fields
EvaluatedAnnotations.Reason: The given annotation is not relevant as it focuses on the design aspect of electromagnetic compatibility, which is not the main focus of the data feature.
